    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-02-27T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-02-27T14:00:00-05:00" n="174"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d174">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.290/2–2751: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Consulate General at Lahore</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-02-27T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 27, 1951—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>73. For Gay. Re Chi representation, London reports indicate little prospect any
                    procedural formula can be worked out for which UK cld cast affirmative vote or
                    even abstention. Re nature Chi representation proposal <gloss target="#t_ECAFE1"
                        >ECAFE</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> leaves ur discretion
                    in light current negotiating situation whether propose postponement motion or
                    support reaffirmation last year’s decision.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
